<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="446" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[199,962,1152,1213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1152,1177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Distribution.</emphasis>
At present known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[725,773,1153,1177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation box="[879,948,1152,1177]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1373,1395]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,577,1330]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1423,558,1349]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Map showing the currently known localities of Shearella spp. ● Shearella alii sp. nov. Shearella lilawati Lehtinen, 1981 ▲ Shearella sanya Lin &amp; Li, 2010 ♦ Shearella selvarani Lehtinen, 1981." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052255/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1188,1213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Remark.</emphasis>
